metadata.name: Maze Runner #10
metadata.description:
This is the second creation from Kakashii.tez!

These pieces were generated all through javascript code and allow the user to interact with their token using the WASD or arrow keys to move around the maze however they want!

These pieces have four different features attached to them:
- Size: The size of the maze. (Tiny, Small, Medium, Large, Huge, GIGANTIC)
- Footprints: If true, enables the user to produce footprints when moving through the maze.
- Teleport: If true, enables the user to teleport randomly in the maze using the "T" key.
- Wallhacks: If true, enables the user to be able to run through any and all walls of the maze.

I hope you all enjoy minting your very own maze, hope the hash rarities are on your side, and above all; have fun in the Maze Runner!

Interaction Notes:
- Use "W" or up arrow to move up.
- Use "A" or left arrow to move left.
- Use "S" or down arrow to move down.
- Use "D" or right arrow to move right.
- If you have the teleport feature, use "T" to teleport at any time.

metadata.name: Tesseract #111
metadata.description:
'Tesseract' is a generative collection drawing on the concept of the cube from oneirology, the interpretation of dreams. In many mythologies and fields of study, the square is considered a 'perfect shape', thus with its abstraction into three isometric dimensions, the cube is seen by some as a representation of the various aspects of the human condition.

In 'Tesseract', the ribbons flowing between the cubes represent the shared experiences that connect us all. No matter how different our lives might be, we all go through the same joys, sorrows, trials, tribulations and experience attachments of varying degrees. 

It is these experiences that bind us together and make us who we are. With these concepts in mind, viewers are invited to interpret each composition as it relates to them and their unique story, from the perspective of that which has been and that which is yet to be experienced.

Press 'S' to save a high resolution PNG at 2400 x 3396 px.

metadata.description:

Primary royalties are split 95-5% between artist and The Processing Foundation.

Secondary royalties go to the minters (99.9% of the 15%).

The preview thumbnails don’t do justice to the artworks. Please run the code to appreciate them better. Also, remember to check the alternate higher resolution renders using [a].

Please get in touch in the event of a blank preview thumbnail.

metadata.name: simple things #97
metadata.description:
There’s beauty in simple things. Sunlight. A reflection on a puddle. The flight of a bird. Observing the clouds. Spending time with loved ones.

To celebrate the re-opening of fxhash, I'd like to contribute with some simple thing to enjoy among friends who rejoin after some time.

Simple things is a piece that is just that: simple things. Nothing fancy here. Simple circles doing simple movement, with simple colours. Maybe the viewer will rejoice in observing them transit on the screen.

It has some controls: you can press “s” to save a png file. You can set a higher resolution pressing “d” followed by 1-9 to increase pixel density (if you get a black image, press “d 0” and start again with a lower number). Simple controls.

It has also colour controls: press z for brightness, x for contrast, g for gamma, b for blur, n for noise followed by + or - to alter their values. You might get some simple variations that you might enjoy. Press a to enable/disable all colour controls (except the noise).

The pieces exhibit simple variations: palettes, circle sizes, density of elements, backgrounds. The colours might be inverted sometimes. The direction of the movement changes also in some pieces. Some are grayscale pieces.

Just like in life, enjoying simple things is sometimes enough to leave behind the noise and our worries. Also like in life, if one wants something extra, they may get it by looking for it...

Artwork by Marcelo Soria-Rodríguez, @msoriaro.
Made in p5.js, and glsl for the image controls.

metadata.name: Sherwood #66
metadata.description:
In the forest, foggy, cloudy weather creates a mysterious, otherworldly atmosphere.

----

Controls:
s or [double click] - save
1 through 8 - set the pixel density for higher resolutions. Base is 2000x1000.
d - increase debug level (none, overlay, overlay + animated drawing)
D - decrease debug level
[plus] or [equal] - increase the edition of the mint (see a new location with the same features)
[minus] - decrease the edition, to a minimum of zero

Made with:
- p5js
- Simplex noise (hills, cleared/forested, grass height, tree size & separation)
- Poisson disk sampling (tree distribution)

metadata.name: Ex Mobius (Vintage Red) #26
metadata.description:
Each output is generated by layering Blender renders.

Each output in this collection has the same "mobius" shape, but the number and positions of the colored regions varies.

All outputs in this collection will have the same color palette (called Vintage Red).

Please allow up to 20 seconds for each image to fully load.

In live mode:
Click/tap the image to make a "Download image" button appear. Click this button to download a 1500x1500px PNG.

Several "Ex Mobius" collections will be released, each with a different color palette.

thought process represents the reach of a single thought.
